aits have fitness consequences (or strong ones at least)."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2442ea911c89187262d6575d739a1ca7?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":5148,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5148/swbarnes2","reputation":1824,"display_name":"swbarnes2"},"score":0,"post_id":17539,"edited":false,"creation_date":1400705551,"comment_id":24017,"body":"There are homo sapiens who can guide themselves with echo location.  How can you argue that it&#39;s impossible to evolve when we humans already have it, without requiring specialized adaptations?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/14616e8dce95f1acfb6596c2558dc215?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":6202,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6202/user813801","reputation":264,"display_name":"user813801"},"score":0,"post_id":17539,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"edited":false,"creation_date":1400736063,"comment_id":24024,"body":"@Chris if the intermediate step is neutral (neither advantageous nor disadvantageous), then you no longer have the pseudo-intelligence of natural selection helping you and it becomes more or less random."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":0,"post_id":17539,"edited":false,"creation_date":1400737039,"comment_id":24030,"body":"Mutations are random."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/14616e8dce95f1acfb6596c2558dc215?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":6202,"link":"ht