deling).<\/p>\n\n<p>Please if you have ever done this kind of data analysis, what should be the appropriate term to describe this approach?<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>Likely candidates<\/strong>  <\/p>\n\n<p><code>Gene expression profiling study<\/code> <\/p>\n\n<p><code>Transcript profiling study<\/code>  <\/p>\n\n<p><code>Transcript Wide Analysis Study<\/code> or <code>TWAS<\/code> for short  <\/p>\n","question_id":17528,"tags":["molecular-biology","bioinformatics","pcr","transcription"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":45,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/76b0e04abd1a60ed2cddee0c49783fac?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":6336,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6336/liamdev631","reputation":31,"display_name":"Liamdev631"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1sIMq.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4108,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4108/remi-b","reputation":22909,"display_name":"Remi.b","accept_rate":88},"score":1,"post_id":16533,"edited":false,"creation_date":1397461885,"comment_id":22317,"body":"+1 good question. I guess that an added chromosome probably come from the duplication of another chromosome yielding to a partial polyploidy. Under this assumption it might be interested to look at the work of Sally Otto on change in ploidy number. I think we might intuitively overconsider the importance of such duplication on the functioning and health of the cell. I would tend to think that the big issue has to do with dosage compensation (amplitude of gene expression). Also, such duplications have the advantage to hide recessive deleterious allele."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/55b2cca3b7a11df3a961d57a68705503?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":43,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/43/daniel-standage","reputation":3502,"display_name":"Daniel