 replicate in any species at all, how do you produce this vector in the first place? (there are ways, but they are laborious)<\/p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>*: I am unable to find an authoritative source for this definition. The other two paragraphs are common knowledge.<\/p>\n","answer_id":17374,"question_id":17373,"up_vote_count":4}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/17373/what-is-a-suicide-plasmid","last_activity_date":1399922415,"creation_date":1399917535,"answer_count":1,"title":"What is a suicide plasmid?","body":"<p>What is a suicide plasmid?<\/p>\n\n<p>Example: <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2737453/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2737453/<\/a> mentions a \"suicide vector\". See also <a href=\"http://www.sci.sdsu.edu/~smaloy/MicrobialGenetics/topics/plasmids/allele-exchange.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.sci.sdsu.edu/~smaloy/MicrobialGenetics/topics/plasmids/allele-exchange.html<\/a> which also mentions them.<\/p>\n","question_id":17373,"tags":["cloning","plasmids","definitions"],"score":3,"accepted_answer_id":17374,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":8393,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1399922415},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1sIMq.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4108,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4108/remi-b","reputation":22909,"display_name":"Remi.b","accept_rate":88},"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/17210/study-case-of-the-inheritance-system-of-oenothera","last_activity_date":1399920211,"creation_date":1399409651,"answer_count":0,"title":"Study case of the inheritance system of Oenothera","body":"<p>I've been told some interesting facts about <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oenothera\" rel=\"nofollow\"><em>oenothera<\/em><\/a>. Apparently in this species some lineages have been through some translocations and in results to these translocations and in consequence, some chromosomes are inherited exclusively through the female function while some other chromosomes are inherited only through the male function.<\/p>\n\n<p>Can you please provide a summary description of how things work in this species concerning the meiosis, the haplo-diplontic life cycle and the recombination?<\/p>\n","question_id":17210,"tags":["evolution","molecular-biology","molecular-genetics","meiosis","recombination"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":39,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1399920211},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d3bb03c123064561f4f8ec6fd36628c0?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":6678,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6678/geekcat","reputation":24,"display_name":"GeekCat"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1sIMq.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4108,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4108/remi-b","reputation":22909,"display_name":"Remi.b","accept_rate":88},"score":0,"post_id":17346,"edited":false,"creation_date":1399840463,"comment_id":23609,"body":"Welcome to StackBiology! Your question very looks like a homework question. You should have a look to the <a href=\"http://biology.stackexchange.com/help/homework\">homework&#39;s questions policy<\/a>. Because you haven&#39;t really showed attempts to answer the question, it is likely that nobody will answer it. Also, you should always try to limit your posts to one question only."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d3bb03c123064561f4f8ec6fd36628c0?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":6678,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6678/geekcat","reputation":24,"display_name":"GeekCat"},"score":0,"post_id":17346,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1sIMq.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4108,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4108/remi-b","reputation":22909,"